Definition: Remove all odd integers from the given list and return the resultant list. Return "[]" if the resultant list is empty. An odd integer is not exactly divisible by 2.

Positive Examples.explanation: 609, 261, 395 are removed from the list because they are odd numbers.
Every value in the input list is odd so an empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains only the odd numbers from the input.
The output only included one instance of the element 10, even though it appears two times in the input list.
